cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DL 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as machine translation and word segmentation. It also incorporates morphology knowledge to preserve linguistic and semantic information in the word structure, which is a common topic in the field of NLP. 

It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it utilizes neural machine translation (NMT) models, which are based on deep learning techniques. 

Furthermore, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as NMT models are a type of neural network and involve training with large amounts of data. 

Lastly, it could be classified under cs.DL (Deep Learning) as it involves the use of deep learning techniques for NMT and word segmentation.
